HEADWORD: Hilding
<hw>Hil"ding</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. a corruption
of <ets>hindling</ets>, dim. of <ets>hind</ets>, adj. Cf. Prov. E.
<ets>hilderling</ets>, <ets>hinderling</ets>. See
<er>Hinderling</er>.]</ety> <def>A base, menial wretch.</def> --
<def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Base; spiritless.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
</def2> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
